Pedipalp. Medium reddish brown, carinae and fingers darker. Orthobothriotaxia “C” (
Vachon 1974
); pattern typical for genus (see
Francke, 1977
). Femur wider than deep. Dorsal internal carina strong, granulose. Dorsal external carina: proximal half moderately strong, sparsely and poorly granulose; distal half tapering gradually to weak. Ventral internal carina strong and granulose. Ventral external carina weak, fading out distally. Dorsal face flat, sparsely granulose, with large strong dark granules. Ventral face flat, smooth. Internal face moderately granulose with large, dark, strong granules.

Pedipalp patella with external carina vestigial to obsolete. Chela rounder, deeper than on the male: carinae fusco-piceous; dorsal margin of manus weakly carinate, coarsely granulose. Digital carina weakly granulose. Dorsal secondary and external secondary carinae weak to moderate, subgranose (
Fig. 6
).
